query: what does it mean if your tsh is low
text: What is TSH? TSH (Thyroid Stimulating Hormone) is a hormone that is produced by the pituitary gland; it is the job of the TSH to stimulate the thyroid and trigger the production of thyroid hormone. High TSH signifies that your thyroid is not producing enough hormone; a low TSH denotes an overproduction of thyroid hormone.

DNA is synthesized naturally while cDNA is a form of DNA which is synthesized by the scientist for their experimental purpose. Genomic DNA contains both introns and exons but cDNA is made up of only exons, which codes for specific functions. cDNAs are much shorter, as introns can span thousands of base pairs.

Transcrition/translation - Exons and introns. Description: In most eukaryotic genes, coding regions (exons) are interrupted by noncoding regions (introns). During transcription, the entire gene is copied into a pre-mRNA, which includes exons and introns.
